00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Here's what science actually says about reconsolidation memory.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:06,400
When we recall a memory, it can change.

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:08,400
This is known as reconsolidation.

4
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:14,000
Every time we remember, our brain rewrites the memory, making us vulnerable to errors.

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,600
Research shows reconsolidation can alter emotions associated with memories.

6
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,600
Feeling different about your past?

7
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:22,000
This means our memories aren’t static.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,200
They evolve, shaping our identity in unexpected ways.

